cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with instance retrieval and recognition using deep learning models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of global features extracted from a multi-attribute recognition model also suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of bilinear CNN to make the model suitable for mobile devices, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
